1. Numeric Literals
2. String Literals
3. Boolean Literals
4. Special Literals

Numeric Literals
Numeric literals can belong to 3 different
numerical types:
• Integer,
• Float, and
• Complex.

String Literals
• It is a sequence of characters surrounded by
quotes, either single, double, or triple quotes for
a string.
• A character literal is a single character
surrounded by single or double quotes.
• 'hello' is the same as "hello"


Boolean Literals
• It can have any of the two values: True or
False.
